    "causal_summary": "Closes the F-001 + F-003 P1 findings from the 012-015 integrated deep-review CONDITIONAL verdict. code_graph_context now blocks the read path on freshness === 'error' BEFORE buildContext() and emits a degraded envelope preserving readiness/canonicalReadiness/trustState/graphAnswersOmitted plus a fallbackDecision: { nextTool: 'rg', reason } matching the code_graph_query shape. code_graph_status now reads getGraphReadinessSnapshot() ahead of graphDb.getStats() and isolates stats into a try/catch so an unavailable DB never suppresses the readiness snapshot. Adds the missing error → missing/unavailable fixture to the shared readiness-contract test suite (F-009) and a new code-graph-degraded-readiness-envelope-parity.vitest.ts that pins F-001 + F-003 contracts plus a cross-handler vocabulary parity sweep (F-008 verification). Decision-record.md ADR-001 documents the shared-vocabulary-handler-local-payload split (F-006/F-008 docs); ADR-002 documents the snapshot-first AND isolate-stats defense-in-depth ordering. All three code-graph handlers (context/status/query) now emit the same canonical readiness fields and route degraded callers to the same rg recovery action.",
